{"questionId":"21454","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>w</mi><mo>=</mo><mtext>i</mtext><mi>z</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>w</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>z</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℂ</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi></math> on the Argand diagram can be transformed to point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>w</mi></math> by two transformations.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Hence, or otherwise, find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi></math> when <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>w</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>−</mo><mtext>i</mtext></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>move&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp;to left to&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mtext>i</mtext></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>then rotate by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>90</mn><mo>°</mo></math>&nbsp;to</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mtext>i</mtext></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>i</mtext><mi>z</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>-</mo><mtext>i</mtext></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>i</mtext><mi>z</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mtext>i</mtext></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>z</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mtext>i</mtext></mrow><mtext>i</mtext></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mtext>i</mtext></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"21454","referenceCode":"21M.1.AHL.TZ1.9c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Hence, or otherwise, find the value of z when w=2−i.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.12—Complex numbers introduction","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.13—Polar and Euler form"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}